A vintage 1970s-style technical illustration showing an interconnected network of glowing lotus flowers, their stems forming an intricate web pattern reminiscent of early computer network diagrams. The flowers are rendered in warm amber, burnt orange, and cream tones against a deep teal background with subtle halftone dot textures. Each lotus bloom contains a soft golden glow at its center, suggesting nodes of information. The composition has the aesthetic of retro technical manuals and engineering blueprints, with delicate linework and a slightly faded, aged paper quality. Small geometric shapes float between the connected flowers like data packets in transit.
